  <content><![CDATA[
The fraction of fossil olfactory receptor genes is significantly higher in all
species with full color vision. This suggests that the evolution of trichromatic
vision --- which allows these primates to detect food, mates, and danger with
visual cues --- has reduced their reliance on the sense of smell.
]]></content>
